text.paragraph:
Systemic allergic reactions, including anaphylaxis, urticaria, angioedema, and generalized rash, have been reported in patients treated with formulations of Mupirocin, including Mupirocin ointment [see Adverse Reactions 
                                 (6.2)
                              ].

As with other antibacterial products, prolonged use of Mupirocin ointment may result in overgrowth of nonsusceptible microorganisms, including fungi [see Dosage and Administration 
                                 (2)
                              ].

